{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 SPOOLER\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 Wire Tension Controller Firmware Specification (C Implementation)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Revision: Rev H \u8211- Finalized TDS Pin Assignment and Analog Integration\line Date: 2026-02-28\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 ============================================================\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 1.\tx360\tab Introduction and System Background\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 SPOOLER is a dedicated embedded motion-control and tension-control firmware system for a wire EDM (Electrical Discharge Machining) machine.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 In a wire EDM system, a thin brass wire (250 \u181?m diameter) is continuously fed from a supply spool (\u8220"feed spool\u8221"), passes through the cutting zone, and is collected on a recovery spool (\u8220"take-up spool\u8221"). Stable and controlled wire tension is essential for maintaining straightness, preventing vibration/whip, avoiding breakage, and maintaining cut accuracy.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Tension is maintained mechanically using a spring-loaded shuttle assembly referred to as the \u8220"dancer\u8221". The dancer moves linearly along a rail in response to changes in wire tension. The position of this dancer is measured using a linear potentiometer (KTR2-R-75).\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The firmware maintains the dancer at a fixed displacement using closed-loop control by adjusting the speed of the recovery spool motor relative to the feed spool motor.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 If the wire breaks, tension collapses and the dancer rapidly moves to its minimum mechanical position. This is detected as a fault condition and the system must stop both motors.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The SPOOLER device communicates with a LinuxCNC host computer via MODBUS/TCP over Ethernet using the onboard W6100 Ethernet controller.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 ============================================================\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 2.\tx360\tab Mechanical System Description\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Wire: - Diameter: 0.25 mm brass EDM wire\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Spool diameters: - Full diameter: ~100 mm - Empty diameter: ~60 mm\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Spool widths: - Feed spool: ~90 mm - Recovery spool: ~50 mm (wire typically accumulates in ~20 mm region)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Drive system: - Stepper: 17HS19-1684S-PG27 - 1.8\u176? step (200 full steps/rev) - 27:1 gearbox - Belt stage: 20T motor pulley \u8594? 80T spool pulley - 4:1 reduction\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Total reduction: 27 \u215? 4 = 108:1\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Full-step resolution at spool: 200 \u215? 108 = 21,600 full steps/rev\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Microstepping multiplier: MISSING INFO Total steps per spool rev: STEPS_PER_SPOOL_REV = 21,600 \u215? MICROSTEP\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 ============================================================\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 3.\tx360\tab Hardware Platform\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 3.1 Microcontroller Board: W6100-EVB-Pico2 (RP2040 + W6100 Ethernet) GPIO16\u8211-GPIO21 are reserved internally for Ethernet and SHALL NOT be used.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 3.2 Stepper Drivers Model: Adafruit TMC2209 - STEP/DIR interface - 3.3V logic compatible - Current setting: MISSING INFO - STEP timing: MISSING INFO\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 3.3 Dancer Position Sensor Model: KTR2-R-75 linear potentiometer - High: 3V3 (pin 36) - Low: AGND (pin 33) - Wiper: GP27 (ADC1, pin 32) Calibration constants: MISSING INFO\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 3.4 Water Quality Sensor Model: Keyestudio KS0429 TDS Meter V1.0\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Electrical characteristics: - Supply: 3.3\u8211-5.5 V - Analog output: 0\u8211-2.3 V - Measurement range: 0\u8211-1000 ppm\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Final pin assignment: - TDS Analog Output: GP26 (ADC0), physical pin 31 - TDS VCC: 3V3 (pin 36) - TDS GND: AGND (pin 33 preferred)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Noise mitigation recommendation: - Optional 1 k\u937? series resistor - Optional 0.1 \u181?F capacitor to AGND at ADC pin\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 ============================================================\par}
